
1. Traditional switch (Before Java 12)
-------------------------------------------
    - switch was only a statement, not an expression.
    - You had to use break; to stop fall-through.
    - It couldnâ€™t directly return a value.


âš  Problems:
- Lots of repetition (result = ...;).
